    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on a bathroom remodel and the drywall seams are looking pretty uneven after the first coat of mud. what's the best way to tape and mud these so i don't end up with visible ridges once i start sanding?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For smooth drywall seams, use fiberglass mesh tape and apply it firmly over the joint before feathering the first coat of joint compound over it. Apply subsequent coats, feathering them out wider and wider, allowing each coat to dry completely between applications. This gradual buildup and wide feathering is key to hiding the tape and creating a seamless surface ready for sanding. Remember that thin coats are always better than one thick, uneven application.",
      "source": "target",
