    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i've been trying to feather it out but i keep noticing these little tiny gaps or cracks appearing in the mud where the tape meets the board. is that just because the mud is shrinking as it dries or am i doing something wrong with the application?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those tiny gaps or cracks are often a sign that the joint compound is drying too quickly or that the application layer is too thick in that specific spot. To combat this, try using a slightly wetter mix for your mud and ensure you are pressing the compound *into* the mesh tape rather than just layering it on top. Feathering outward and allowing the mud to cure slowly helps minimize shrinkage cracks and ensures a consistent bond.",
      "source": "target",
